========================================================================
  PART 2: CONCENTRATION VIA FOURIER
  We proved: Var(H)/Mean(H)^2 = 2(n-2)/(n(n-1)) + level-4 correction
========================================================================

  Chebyshev bound: Pr[|H - mu| >= t*sigma] <= 1/t^2

  Our formula:
    mu = n!/2^{n-1}
    sigma^2 = mu^2 * (2(n-2)/(n(n-1)) + epsilon_n)

  where epsilon_n = level-4 contribution >= 0, and epsilon_n = 0 at n=3,4.

  So sigma = mu * sqrt(2(n-2)/(n(n-1)) + epsilon_n)
  ~ mu * sqrt(2/n) for large n.

  Chebyshev at k standard deviations:
    Pr[|H - mu| >= k*sigma] <= 1/k^2


  n=3: mu=1.5000, sigma=0.8660
    sigma/mu = 0.577350 (= sqrt(Var/Mean^2))
    CV (coefficient of variation) = 0.577350
    Pr[|H-mu| < 1*sigma] = 0.750000 (Chebyshev >= 0.0000)
    Pr[|H-mu| < 2*sigma] = 1.000000 (Chebyshev >= 0.7500)
    Pr[|H-mu| < 3*sigma] = 1.000000 (Chebyshev >= 0.8889)

  n=4: mu=3.0000, sigma=1.7321
    sigma/mu = 0.577350 (= sqrt(Var/Mean^2))
    CV (coefficient of variation) = 0.577350
    Pr[|H-mu| < 1*sigma] = 0.250000 (Chebyshev >= 0.0000)
    Pr[|H-mu| < 2*sigma] = 1.000000 (Chebyshev >= 0.7500)
    Pr[|H-mu| < 3*sigma] = 1.000000 (Chebyshev >= 0.8889)

  n=5: mu=7.5000, sigma=4.2205
    sigma/mu = 0.562731 (= sqrt(Var/Mean^2))
    CV (coefficient of variation) = 0.562731
    Pr[|H-mu| < 1*sigma] = 0.585938 (Chebyshev >= 0.0000)
    Pr[|H-mu| < 2*sigma] = 1.000000 (Chebyshev >= 0.7500)
    Pr[|H-mu| < 3*sigma] = 1.000000 (Chebyshev >= 0.8889)

