========================================================================
  PART 8: THE FIBONACCI/GOLDEN RATIO IN TOURNAMENT STATISTICS
  I(Omega, 1/phi) evaluates the independence poly at golden ratio
========================================================================
  phi = 1.6180339887
  1/phi = 0.6180339887
  phi^2 = phi + 1 = 2.6180339887
  KEY: [2]_q = q + q^-1 = 1/phi when q = e^(2*pi*i/5)
       So I(Omega, 1/phi) is the quantum group evaluation at level 5!

  n=3: I(Omega, 1/phi) distribution:
    I=1.000000 (H=1): 6 tournaments
    I=1.618034 (H=3): 2 tournaments
    Mean I(1/phi) = 1.154508
    = 1 + Mean(alpha_1)/phi = 1 + 0.2500/1.6180
    Var(I(1/phi)) = 0.071619
    Predicted: (1/phi)^2 * Var(H)/4 = 0.071619
    Match: True
    Var/Mean^2 at x=2: 0.333333
    Var/Mean^2 at x=1/phi: 0.053732

  n=4: I(Omega, 1/phi) distribution:
    I=1.000000 (H=1): 24 tournaments
    I=1.618034 (H=3): 16 tournaments
    I=2.236068 (H=5): 24 tournaments
    Mean I(1/phi) = 1.618034
    = 1 + Mean(alpha_1)/phi = 1 + 1.0000/1.6180
    Var(I(1/phi)) = 0.286475
    Predicted: (1/phi)^2 * Var(H)/4 = 0.286475
    Match: True
    Var/Mean^2 at x=2: 0.333333
    Var/Mean^2 at x=1/phi: 0.109424

  n=5: I(Omega, 1/phi) distribution:
    I=1.000000 (H=1): 120 tournaments
    I=1.618034 (H=3): 120 tournaments
    I=2.236068 (H=5): 240 tournaments
    I=3.472136 (H=9): 240 tournaments
    I=4.090170 (H=11): 120 tournaments
    I=4.708204 (H=13): 120 tournaments
    I=5.326238 (H=15): 64 tournaments
    Mean I(1/phi) = 3.008610
    = 1 + Mean(alpha_1)/phi = 1 + 3.2500/1.6180
    Var(I(1/phi)) = 1.700942
    Predicted: (1/phi)^2 * Var(H)/4 = 1.700942
    Match: True
    Var/Mean^2 at x=2: 0.316667
    Var/Mean^2 at x=1/phi: 0.187913

